.TH KALEIDUX-DAEMON 1 "JANUARY 2026" "0.0.1-kneecap" "Kaleidux Manual"
.SH NAME
kaleidux-daemon \- High-performance hardware-accelerated wallpaper daemon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kaleidux-daemon
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B kaleidux-daemon
is a sophisticated wallpaper daemon for Wayland and X11 that specializes in smooth, hardware-accelerated transitions. It provides seamless blending between high-resolution images and videos using WGPU and GStreamer.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Show version information.
.TP
.B \-\-demo
Start the daemon in demo mode, cycling through built-in transitions and sample content.
.TP
.B \-\-log \fI<LOG>\fR
Set the logging verbosity (e.g., debug, info, warn) or specify a log file destination.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help information.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/kaleidux/config.toml
The main configuration file where monitors, content paths, and transitions are defined.
.TP
.I ~/.config/kaleidux/logs/
Directory containing daemon logs if file logging is enabled.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR kldctl (1)
